00:00:01.790 --> 00:00:03.490
Prof: So welcome.
 

00:00:03.490 --> 00:00:11.760
This is a course on Foundations
of Modern Social Thought.

00:00:11.760 --> 00:00:17.449
It has a sociology number,
a political science number,

00:00:17.449 --> 00:00:20.240
and a humanities number.
 

00:00:20.240 --> 00:00:23.300
And my name is Iván
Szelényi.

00:00:23.300 --> 00:00:26.852
I'm a professor of sociology,
a professor of political

00:00:26.852 --> 00:00:31.503
science,
and it is my honor that I can

00:00:31.503 --> 00:00:37.980
introduce you to some of the
Founding Fathers--

00:00:37.980 --> 00:00:41.580
I'm afraid they are all fathers
right,

00:00:41.580 --> 00:00:46.741
no mothers among them;
I will tell you why not--of

00:00:46.741 --> 00:00:50.090
modern social thought.
 

00:00:50.090 --> 00:00:55.064
It's basically theories,
starting from the sixteenth

00:00:55.064 --> 00:01:00.429
century and ending up in the
early twentieth century.

00:01:00.429 --> 00:01:33.720
 
 

00:01:33.720 --> 00:01:38.409
The first author on our list,
Thomas Hobbes,

00:01:38.409 --> 00:01:44.078
did a lot of work on optics and
has been in a violent

00:01:44.078 --> 00:01:47.459
controversy with Descartes.
 

00:01:47.459 --> 00:01:52.772
So those of you who are in
natural sciences are probably

00:01:52.772 --> 00:01:58.569
familiar with Descartes and his
pioneering work on optics.

00:01:58.569 --> 00:02:03.510
John Locke, for those of you
who aspire to become a doctor,

00:02:03.510 --> 00:02:11.873
was actually studying medicine
and performed a surgery on a

00:02:11.873 --> 00:02:17.210
very well-known English
politician.

00:02:17.210 --> 00:02:21.888
A quite successful surgery,
though even today doctors quite

00:02:21.888 --> 00:02:26.163
don't know whether this
politician survived because of

00:02:26.163 --> 00:02:29.389
good luck or because of the
surgery.

00:02:29.389 --> 00:02:32.788
Anyway, the point I'm trying to
make,

00:02:32.788 --> 00:02:36.605
in the early sixteenth,
seventeenth,

00:02:36.605 --> 00:02:41.949
eighteenth centuries,
sciences and social sciences

00:02:41.949 --> 00:02:46.530
are not separated from each
other yet.

00:02:46.530 --> 00:02:51.972
Jean Jacques Rousseau,
a real pain in the neck but an

00:02:51.972 --> 00:02:58.067
extremely smart guy,
he also wrote an important book

00:02:58.067 --> 00:03:03.538
which dealt with sciences and
social studies.

00:03:03.538 --> 00:03:09.073
It's really by the kind of late
eighteenth century that people

00:03:09.073 --> 00:03:13.879
are beginning to identify as
studying society or human

00:03:13.879 --> 00:03:15.060
behavior.
 

00:03:15.060 --> 00:03:19.077
But even then,
until the very last author--

00:03:19.077 --> 00:03:22.902
what we have here,
Emile Durkheim--people

00:03:22.902 --> 00:03:27.590
identified themselves with a
number of approaches,

00:03:27.590 --> 00:03:30.460
disciplinary approaches.
 

00:03:30.460 --> 00:03:33.787
There were social scientists,
all right, or philosophers,

00:03:33.787 --> 00:03:34.500
all right.
 

00:03:34.500 --> 00:03:39.049
The difference between
philosophy and social science is

00:03:39.049 --> 00:03:40.650
a very vague one.
 

00:03:40.650 --> 00:03:48.331
So they're beginning to
distinguish themselves

00:03:48.331 --> 00:03:56.014
increasingly from sciences,
but they are still

00:03:56.014 --> 00:03:59.770
multidisciplinary.
 

00:03:59.770 --> 00:04:01.689
Who is Karl Marx, you know?
 

00:04:01.689 --> 00:04:03.689
He is a philosopher.
 

00:04:03.689 --> 00:04:05.860
He's an economist.
 

00:04:05.860 --> 00:04:09.258
He is a political scientist.
 

00:04:09.258 --> 00:04:13.677
Sociologists name him as one of
the Founding Fathers of

00:04:13.677 --> 00:04:14.658
sociology.
 

00:04:14.658 --> 00:04:22.480
Max Weber, he identified
himself as a legal theorist.

00:04:22.480 --> 00:04:26.060
He was studying economic
history.

00:04:26.060 --> 00:04:31.574
I think primarily he identified
himself, early in life,

00:04:31.574 --> 00:04:36.069
as an economist,
as an economic historian;

00:04:36.069 --> 00:04:40.569
